# Project Instructions
- Always use Context7 MCP when I need library/API documentation, code generation, setup or configuration steps.
- Refer to `.agent/knowledge/CONTEXT7_MCP.md` for detailed usage of the Context7 tools.
- **Project Management**: Always check `.agent/management/BACKLOG.md` before starting new tasks. Follow workflows in `.agent/workflows/` for capturing notes, bugs, and ideas to ensure nothing is lost.
- **Git Safety**: NEVER use the `&&` operator to chain git commands. Execute each git command (add, commit, push) as a separate process to avoid shell-specific parser errors.
- **Deep Analysis Protocol**: Before proposing or implementing large-scale refactorings, restructurings, or high-complexity changes, you MUST explicitly ask the user if they want a deep, forensic analysis first. Never sacrifice architectural integrity for token efficiency.

